WHAT IS IT?
-----------

  'Tri_Add' is a mathematical puzzle where you add the numbers
of a pyramid-like board in order to equal the total of the game.

  You start from the top and you go down on each row. The lower
tile you choose must always be linked either at left or at right
from the upper choosen tile. As you descend in the pyramid, the
selected tiles form a 'path'.

  The game adds the total from the selected tiles and displays it
under the pyramid. When you get to the lowest row and your total
equals the total of the game, you win.

  You can go back anytime or even restart from the top of the
pyramid. If you restart from a tile lower than the top, the new
choosen tiles must always be linked with an upper selected one.
When you select a tile that is located higher than the last
choosen tiles, all the path created earlier from that row will be
erased.

  Have fun!

